that's what you want?

47:42.760 --> 47:45.160
Yes.

48:09.320 --> 48:11.240
Ok. Get her up.

48:21.320 --> 48:23.240
Blow out!

48:24.200 --> 48:26.120
Get away!
Blow out!

48:26.120 --> 48:27.560
Terry!

48:27.560 --> 48:28.520
Terry!

48:36.760 --> 48:38.200
Terry! Terry!

48:41.480 --> 48:42.440
Terry!

48:48.520 --> 48:50.120
Talk to me, will you?

49:07.720 --> 49:08.680
Watch out!

49:10.280 --> 49:12.200
Jan!

49:12.200 --> 49:15.560
Go get... get a medic!

49:33.640 --> 49:36.520
I don't know what kind of
condition he's in.

49:36.520 --> 49:39.800
I think it's very serious, though.

49:39.800 --> 49:41.720
I don't quite know.

49:48.440 --> 49:51.800
It's Jan. There's been
an accident on the rig.

50:44.680 --> 50:47.080
Jan, can you hear me?

50:51.400 --> 50:53.320
Oh.

51:01.240 --> 51:03.160
What are you doing?

51:03.160 --> 51:05.560
I'm holding your hand.

51:05.560 --> 51:07.000
Don't touch me.

51:07.000 --> 51:08.440
Don't touch me!

51:08.440 --> 51:09.880
Jan, relax.
Just take...

51:22.600 --> 51:24.040
Sit down here.

51:28.360 --> 51:30.760
All right.
All right.

51:30.760 --> 51:33.160
Shh. Deep breath.

51:33.160 --> 51:35.560
Hello.
Talk to me, darling.

51:35.560 --> 51:37.480
Talk to me.

51:37.480 --> 51:38.920
Talk to me.

51:39.400 --> 51:40.840
Come on.
It's all right.

51:43.240 --> 51:45.160
It's all right.
It's going to be all right.

52:04.500 --> 52:06.420
Uh, they're going
to operate straightaway.

52:06.420 --> 52:08.820
It will be a few hours,...

52:09.300 --> 52:10.260
...so I think we better wait...

52:10.260 --> 52:12.180
Bess.

52:12.180 --> 52:15.060
Bess, you can't go in there.

52:15.060 --> 52:16.500
It's not allowed.
I want to be with him.

52:16.500 --> 52:17.460
I know you do.
I know.

52:17.460 --> 52:18.420
But come on. Come with me.
Come on.

52:18.420 --> 52:20.820
No. I want to see him
all the time.

52:20.820 --> 52:23.700
Bess, it's not a good idea.
Come on.

52:23.700 --> 52:26.580
Bess. Bess, please,
you can't stay here.

52:27.060 --> 52:28.500
It's just not possible.

52:28.500 --> 52:29.460
Bess!

52:29.460 --> 52:31.380
Can I have
a word with you?

52:31.380 --> 52:34.740
Stay there, all right?
Don't move.

53:02.180 --> 53:05.060
I want you
to pray with me.

53:07.460 --> 53:08.740
But...

53:08.900 --> 53:10.340
Please.

53:24.420 --> 53:28.740
Dear god,
we pray that you…

53:29.220 --> 53:32.100
…will hold your hand
over Jan…

53:32.580 --> 53:35.940
…and not let him die.

53:35.940 --> 53:37.380
Amen.

54:11.220 --> 54:14.580
Mrs. Nyman, will you please
come with me?

54:42.900 --> 54:45.300
Will he live?

54:45.300 --> 54:52.020
We have stabilized your husband's
condition for the time being.

54:54.900 --> 54:57.300
Will he live?

54:57.300 --> 55:00.180
Yes. Yes, Bess,
He will live.

55:07.860 --> 55:11.220
Your husband suffered
very serious injuries.

55:13.140 --> 55:16.500
Life shouldn't always
be preserved at any cost.

55:18.660 --> 55:20.580
What do you mean?

55:23.460 --> 55:25.860
Um, well, the doctor
means, Bess...

55:25.860 --> 55:29.700
...that, um, sometimes...

55:30.180 --> 55:33.060
...in some cases when
life isn't worth living,...

55:33.060 --> 55:36.420
...then it may
be better to die.

55:41.220 --> 55:46.980
You don't know Jan, or you
could not say such a thing.

55:48.420 --> 55:51.780
