55:58.980 --> 56:02.820
Yes. He will live,
it seems.

56:12.020 --> 56:13.620
Father.

56:15.060 --> 56:17.460
Are you there?

56:17.460 --> 56:19.380
Are you still there?

56:23.700 --> 56:26.100
Of course I am, Bess.

56:26.100 --> 56:27.540
You know that.

56:36.660 --> 56:39.060
What's happening?

56:44.340 --> 56:47.700
You wanted Jan home.

56:51.060 --> 56:53.460
I've changed my mind.

56:53.460 --> 56:55.380
Why did I ask for that?

56:58.260 --> 56:59.700
Because you're...

57:00.180 --> 57:02.580
...a stupid little girl, Bess.

57:02.580 --> 57:05.460
I had to test you.

57:05.460 --> 57:09.300
Your love for Jan
has been put to the test.

57:17.460 --> 57:18.900
Thank you…

57:18.900 --> 57:20.820
…for not letting him die.

57:25.620 --> 57:27.540
You're welcome, Bess.

57:42.500 --> 57:48.260
<i>he said
"there is no reason</i>

57:48.260 --> 57:51.140
<i>And the truth
is plain to see"</i>

57:54.020 --> 57:57.860
<i>But I wandered
through my playing cards</i>

58:00.260 --> 58:03.620
<i>And would not let her be</i>

58:06.500 --> 58:10.340
<i>One of 16 vestal virgins</i>

58:12.740 --> 58:15.620
<i>Who were leaving
for the coast</i>

58:18.980 --> 58:23.300
<i>And although
my eyes were open</i>

58:25.220 --> 58:28.580
<i>They might just as well
have been closed</i>

58:28.580 --> 58:30.980
<i>And so it was...</i>

58:30.980 --> 58:34.820
I would say to you...

58:34.820 --> 58:38.180
...that if there is one of
these commandments...

58:38.180 --> 58:43.460
...which you do not love
and do not obey,...

58:43.460 --> 58:47.300
...you have no place
at the Lord's table.

59:10.940 --> 59:12.380
When did you get back?

59:12.380 --> 59:13.820
I came back with Jan.

59:14.300 --> 59:16.220
Oh, it's good to see you.

59:32.340 --> 59:35.100
Oh, surf's up!

59:35.100 --> 59:36.180
Hi.

59:36.180 --> 59:37.140
Hi, guys.

59:37.620 --> 59:38.580
How you doing, buddy?

59:38.580 --> 59:40.500
Well, fine.
How are you?

59:40.500 --> 59:41.940
Ok.

59:44.820 --> 59:46.260
Did you find anything?

59:46.740 --> 59:48.180
Gas.

59:48.180 --> 59:49.620
Nothing really.

59:49.620 --> 59:51.540
Ha ha!
Guess what, now.

59:51.540 --> 59:52.980
We're heading up north.

59:52.980 --> 59:54.420
Well, north,
that's good.

59:54.900 --> 59:57.300
That's where you
always said the oil was.

59:57.660 --> 59:59.580
What are you doing here, anyway?

59:59.580 --> 01:00:01.500
We're meant to be
out drilling.

01:00:02.940 --> 01:00:04.380
I just felt like

01:00:04.380 --> 01:00:06.780
Putting my feet up
for a while.

01:00:06.900 --> 01:00:10.260
I didn't trust you
two guys out there alone.

01:00:21.540 --> 01:00:23.460
Oh, my...

01:00:23.460 --> 01:00:26.340
My arms aren't ok, so...

01:00:26.340 --> 01:00:28.740
I'm not thirsty, anyway.

01:00:30.660 --> 01:00:33.540
Bullshit!

01:00:37.500 --> 01:00:39.420
Hey, come on.

01:00:39.420 --> 01:00:40.860
Come on.

01:00:43.260 --> 01:00:45.180
Oh, man, sorry.

01:00:51.420 --> 01:00:52.860
Oh, man, sorry.

01:00:53.340 --> 01:00:54.780
Ok.

01:00:54.780 --> 01:00:56.700
Thank you.

01:01:07.020 --> 01:01:10.860
I'm not really supposed to
have any visitors, so...

01:01:10.860 --> 01:01:13.260
We really don't have
the time, either.

01:01:13.260 --> 01:01:15.180
Ha ha ha! Ok.

01:01:15.180 --> 01:01:17.100
You take care of yourself, huh?

01:01:17.580 --> 01:01:19.980
Take care.
Get well soon.

01:01:19.980 --> 01:01:21.420
See you, guys.

01:01:32.460 --> 01:01:34.860
Will you do
something for me?

01:01:34.860 --> 01:01:36.300
Yes.

01:01:38.700 --> 01:01:40.620
The next time you come,...

01:01:40.620 --> 01:01:42.060
...could you wear something more...

01:01:43.980 --> 01:01:45.900
More loose...

01:01:48.300 --> 01:01:50.700
So I, uh...

01:01:50.700 --> 01:01:53.100
So I won't have to see your body.

01:02:30.060 --> 01:02:32.940
Bess, you'll have to go now...

01:02:32.940 --> 01:02:34.860
...because Jan needs to rest.

01:02:35.340 --> 01:02:36.780
All right.

01:02:48.540 --> 01:02:50.940
You shouldn't get him
too overemotional, you know.

01:02:50.940 --> 01:02:52.860
It's not good for him.

01:02:52.860 --> 01:02:55.260
I'm sorry.

01:02:55.260 --> 01:02:57.660
You got to cheer him up.

01:03:01.020 --> 01:03:02.940
Is he asleep now?

01:03:02.940 --> 01:03:04.860
Well, he should be...

01:03:05.340 --> 01:03:07.260
…the amount I've given him.

01:03:08.820 --> 01:03:10.260
Would it be all right...

01:03:10.260 --> 01:03:13.140
...If I went and had
a look at him?

01:03:32.340 --> 01:03:34.740
I love you, Jan.

01:03:42.900 --> 01:03:46.740
I love you, too, Bess.

01:03:46.740 --> 01:03:50.100
You are the love of my life.

01:04:09.820 --> 01:04:11.740
Bess.

01:04:14.620 --> 01:04:16.540
Where have you been?

01:04:16.540 --> 01:04:18.940
I've been to the church.

01:04:21.820 --> 01:04:24.220
What, at 2:00 in the morning?

01:04:29.980 --> 01:04:32.380
I don't want you
getting ill again...

01:04:32.860 --> 01:04:34.300
…like you did
when Sam died.

01:04:34.300 --> 01:04:36.220
I said I've been
to the church.

01:04:36.220 --> 01:04:38.140
It has nothing to do
with the church.

01:04:38.620 --> 01:04:41.500
Did you hear what I said?
Did you?

01:04:42.940 --> 01:04:45.340
I don't want you
to get ill again

01:04:45.340 --> 01:04:47.740
Like you did when Sam died.

01:04:47.740 --> 01:04:51.100
I've had a word with
Dr. Richardson, all right?

01:04:51.100 --> 01:04:53.980
And he says
he could see you tomorrow.

01:04:53.980 --> 01:04:56.380
Oh, can he?

01:05:03.580 --> 01:05:06.460
Bess, would you like
to come in?

01:05:27.700 --> 01:05:30.100
Dodo said I had to come.

01:05:30.100 --> 01:05:33.820
She has this idea
about me treating you.

01:05:36.700 --> 01:05:40.060
My predecessor admitted you
a few years ago.

01:05:41.020 --> 01:05:43.420
Well, why did he do that?

01:05:43.900 --> 01:05:45.820
I don't know.

01:05:45.820 --> 01:05:48.220
No, nor do I.

01:05:48.220 --> 01:05:51.100
You were upset because
your brother had died...

01:05:51.100 --> 01:05:54.700
...and now you're upset
because your husband's ill.

01:05:54.700 --> 01:05:56.620
Nothing unusual about that.

01:05:59.020 --> 01:06:01.900
Am I not going to
have some pills?

01:06:02.380 --> 01:06:04.300
I'm probably not like
your old doctor.

01:06:04.300 --> 01:06:06.700
I don't think that people
should be given pills...

01:06:06.700 --> 01:06:08.620
...just because they do
what's only natural.

01:06:09.820 --> 01:06:12.700
Maybe showing what you feel
isn't the done thing...

01:06:12.700 --> 01:06:14.140
...from where you come from,...

01:06:14.140 --> 01:06:16.540
...but it's certainly no disease.

01:06:17.500 --> 01:06:20.380
What...happened on the rig...

01:06:20.380 --> 01:06:22.300
...was my fault.

01:06:23.740 --> 01:06:25.180
How come?

01:06:27.100 --> 01:06:29.980
I prayed to God
to send him home.

01:06:32.380 --> 01:06:34.300
Well...

01:06:37.660 --> 01:06:39.580
Well...

01:06:39.580 --> 01:06:42.460
What powers you possess.

01:06:42.460 --> 01:06:43.900
Do you really...

01:06:44.380 --> 01:06:46.780
Do you really believe
that you possess such powers?

01:06:48.220 --> 01:06:51.940
I know you people believe
a lot about yourselves.

01:06:51.940 --> 01:06:53.380
Bess...

01:06:53.380 --> 01:06:55.780
Perhaps you should do
a bit of grieving…

01:06:55.780 --> 01:06:57.220
…for yourself
instead of him.

01:06:57.700 --> 01:06:59.620
I think you should
come and see me...

01:06:59.620 --> 01:07:01.540
...now and again
if you feel like it.

01:07:07.180 --> 01:07:09.100
I'm sorry.

01:07:09.100 --> 01:07:10.540
Oh. Ha ha!

01:07:10.540 --> 01:07:11.980
Come on.

01:07:13.900 --> 01:07:16.660
Well, things will pick up
once he gets home again.

